abstract: Dime-size clinging jellyfish, species that packs a powerful sting and is usually found in Pacific Ocean, has been spotted in New Jersey; mostly found in areas with eelgrass beds, experts say clinging jellyfish are unlikely to appear where most people swim, like sandy beaches and open coastline.
lead_paragraph: Without invitation or a clear explanation, this small-but-mighty variety of jellyfish has been found for the first time in the Garden State.

headline.main: An Unwelcome Tourist Arrives in New Jersey: Clinging Jellyfish
headline.print_headline: A First-Time Tourist Has Arrived in New Jersey. Fortunately, It Is Not a Fan of the Beach.
